1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000

2
00:00:45,710 --> 00:00:49,380

3
00:00:49,380 --> 00:00:55,440

4
00:00:58,120 --> 00:01:00,230
Sae Bom is here, right?

5
00:01:02,140 --> 00:01:05,580
She is a little busy right now.

6
00:01:05,580 --> 00:01:08,150
She will be out soon. Please wait.

7
00:01:11,260 --> 00:01:15,970
Did you take the drug? The one you bought at the gym?

8
00:01:17,540 --> 00:01:22,290
If you messed with Sae Bom, you're dead.

9
00:01:26,330 --> 00:01:28,840
It seems like there has been a misunderstanding.

10
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:31,350
Then open this door right now.

11
00:01:52,270 --> 00:01:53,820
Where is Sae Bom?

12
00:01:53,820 --> 00:01:56,180
Sae Bom!

13
00:01:56,180 --> 00:01:57,630
What?

14
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:02,650
Hyun, are you hungry, too?

15
00:02:02,650 --> 00:02:04,260
What?

16
00:02:17,210 --> 00:02:21,090
Well, I came here because I missed you.

17
00:02:21,090 --> 00:02:22,520
- Help me out. 
 - What?

18
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:23,830
- I said help me out. Stand up. 
 - What?

19
00:02:23,830 --> 00:02:25,540
Come on, stand up.

20
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:30,880
We are newlyweds so I missed her a lot.

21
00:02:34,660 --> 00:02:39,820
I mean, he worries about me even if he doesn't see me for a short while.

22
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:46,190
You must... You must love her very much.

23
00:02:47,890 --> 00:02:49,570
Of course.

24
00:03:00,790 --> 00:03:03,840
What is it? Why?

25
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:05,410
Do you want some?

26
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:08,900
He has so many interesting things. Look.

27
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:11,650
He also has a lot of food.

28
00:03:11,650 --> 00:03:15,320
- Weren't there any problems? 
 - No.

29
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:20,740

30
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:23,620

31
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:25,340
Then I'll see you later.

32
00:03:25,340 --> 00:03:27,550
Thank you for this.

33
00:03:29,830 --> 00:03:32,910
Hey, why did you do that? If he gets annoyed, he will hold a grudge for a long time.

34
00:03:32,910 --> 00:03:37,080
The gym trainer sold NEXT to that guy.

35
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:39,900
Don't turn around. He might be watching us right now.

36
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:43,960
No way. He is not some spy or anything...

37
00:03:49,690 --> 00:03:51,090
Let me have a look at you.

38
00:03:51,090 --> 00:03:53,400
Did you get hurt anywhere? Did you get a scratch or...

39
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:56,920
feel a pinch behind your neck? Anything like that?

40
00:04:01,310 --> 00:04:03,250
This isn't healing...

41
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:06,610
It has almost healed. It is not even that noticeable.

42
00:04:08,750 --> 00:04:13,260
Anyway, did anything seem strange besides the interior decoration?

43
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:18,050
He said his father was a diplomat so he traveled through Africa and the Middle East during his childhood.

44
00:04:18,050 --> 00:04:20,750
And that's how he realized that the end of the earth isn't too far off.

45
00:04:20,750 --> 00:04:22,140
So he is strange.

46
00:04:22,140 --> 00:04:25,480
But he seems nice. He gave me all this, too.

47
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:31,290
These are super delicious when you're hungry.

48
00:04:31,290 --> 00:04:34,510
Everything is delicious when you're hungry.

49
00:04:42,220 --> 00:04:44,360
Who is it?

50
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,730
Hi.

51
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:23,460
Little Girl, are you alone?

52
00:05:23,460 --> 00:05:26,600
- Who are you, Ahjussi? 
 - Don't you know me?

53
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,970
You know I'm your mom's friend.

54
00:05:28,970 --> 00:05:31,830
Can you open this?

55
00:05:31,830 --> 00:05:33,680
If you just unlock...

56
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:42,660
 Little Girl, why did you do that? You hurt my hand!

57
00:05:43,830 --> 00:05:46,310
I'm sorry. Can you open the door for me?

58
00:05:46,310 --> 00:05:48,990
 I'm not a bad person.

59
00:05:48,990 --> 00:05:52,890
 Are you listening to what I'm saying?

60
00:05:54,690 --> 00:05:57,760
Do you have any medicine or something?

61
00:05:57,760 --> 00:06:00,210
Where did you get hurt?

62
00:06:05,860 --> 00:06:08,250
How did you get in here?

63
00:06:10,630 --> 00:06:14,880
The first-floor door was open.

64
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:17,770
I'm not trying to do anything bad.

65
00:06:19,620 --> 00:06:22,160
I haven't even bitten anyone.

66
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:25,760
I just feel so lonely and feel frustrated.

67
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:28,990
Try to say that nonsense after wiping the blood off your mouth.

68
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:33,560
Who did you bite?

69
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:38,420
Just slightly...

70
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:41,370
I didn't bite a lot.

71
00:06:42,950 --> 00:06:46,630
He survived and ran away.

72
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:04,120
Leave at the count of three.

73
00:07:05,530 --> 00:07:07,160
One,

74
00:07:07,940 --> 00:07:11,620
two, three!

75
00:07:19,460 --> 00:07:21,660
Seo Yoon, it is Unni.

76
00:07:25,590 --> 00:07:28,870
Seo Yoon, it is Unni Sae Bom.

77
00:07:32,990 --> 00:07:36,160
Did that man leave?

78
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,930
Yes.

79
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:41,620
- Where is Ahjussi Jung Gook? 
 - On the second floor.

80
00:07:41,620 --> 00:07:45,600
He went down because we are out of kitchen cleaners and toothpaste.

81
00:07:46,870 --> 00:07:50,660
I will be right back. Don't open the door no matter who asks you to open it.

82
00:07:50,660 --> 00:07:52,660
Just like how you did. Okay?

83
00:07:52,660 --> 00:07:54,790
You did well, Seo Yoon.

84
00:07:54,790 --> 00:07:59,230
Eat this and calm yourself down. Okay?

85
00:07:59,230 --> 00:08:01,160
- I will be right back. 
 - Okay.

86
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:03,360
- I will be right back. 
 - Okay.

87
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:14,370
How did he get inside?

88
00:08:14,370 --> 00:08:17,390
There may be more inside. I have to look through the building.

89
00:08:23,430 --> 00:08:28,420
More important, I wonder whose blood he has on him.

90
00:08:29,180 --> 00:08:30,860
 Ahjumma.

91
00:08:30,860 --> 00:08:35,770
Ahjumma, I'm not infected. Really!

92
00:08:35,770 --> 00:08:39,870
Actually, I came here because the ahjumma from unit 1205 said she would give me money,

93
00:08:39,870 --> 00:08:44,190
 but with this lockdown and infection... What the hell is going on here?

94
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:48,030
Ahjumma, I will... I will help you.

95
00:08:48,030 --> 00:08:51,030
I will help you so we can both get out. Think about it. Have I...

96
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:53,440
Have I done anything strange? I haven't!

97
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:55,490
I just sat here quietly, didn't I?

98
00:08:55,490 --> 00:08:57,630
- Aren't you thirsty? 
 - What?

99
00:08:57,630 --> 00:08:59,390
Look.

100
00:08:59,390 --> 00:09:01,400
I'm fine, right?

101
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:05,930
I'm perfectly fine.

102
00:09:05,930 --> 00:09:07,720
I look fine, right?

103
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:11,830
 I will definitely help you, Ahjumma...

104
00:09:11,830 --> 00:09:14,460
 Ahjumma, you'll never be able to get out by yourself. Really.

105
00:09:14,460 --> 00:09:16,910
 Ahjumma, help me out just this once.

106
00:09:24,490 --> 00:09:26,040
Thank you.

107
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:28,300
I will trust you just this once.

108
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:49,020
Are you okay?

109
00:09:53,730 --> 00:09:56,000
Even if I drink...

110
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:59,800
Even if I drink, I'm still thirsty... What am I supposed to do?

111
00:10:25,090 --> 00:10:28,830
Ahjumma, I'm all better now.

112
00:10:30,090 --> 00:10:33,630
Come over here. We have to go upstairs together.

113
00:10:33,630 --> 00:10:36,190
Will you keep standing there

114
00:10:36,190 --> 00:10:38,580
until the infected people come?

115
00:10:38,580 --> 00:10:42,530
Ahjumma, come on. Trust me!

116
00:11:20,530 --> 00:11:22,420
Hyun...

117
00:11:27,950 --> 00:11:29,650
Let's hurry.

118
00:11:43,140 --> 00:11:45,470
It is Na Soo Min's phone.

119
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:00,450

120
00:12:13,030 --> 00:12:17,630
I mean, no matter how much I drink...

121
00:12:18,980 --> 00:12:20,680
I feel parched.

122
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:23,300
Where are Na Soo Min and Na Hyun Kyung?

123
00:12:23,300 --> 00:12:25,560
I don't know, either.

124
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:30,510
Kim Seung Beom, inhale and exhale deeply.

125
00:12:30,510 --> 00:12:34,820
Your desire will subside if you can just control your breathing.

126
00:12:34,820 --> 00:12:36,930
I mean...

127
00:12:36,930 --> 00:12:41,810
I feel more thirsty the more I drink...

128
00:12:41,810 --> 00:12:44,600
Do you know how tough that is when I know what I need to drink to quench my thirst?

129
00:12:46,810 --> 00:12:50,700
when I know what I need to drink to quench my thirst?

130
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:53,860
What do you think will quench your thirst?

131
00:12:57,420 --> 00:12:59,250
Human blood?

132
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:05,370
But how would you know that?

133
00:13:06,210 --> 00:13:07,670
Who told you that?

134
00:13:07,670 --> 00:13:10,330
I just know.

135
00:13:10,330 --> 00:13:15,140
When I see a pale neck, I become more thirsty.

136
00:14:21,460 --> 00:14:24,400
Do you think I'm not using a gun because I don't have one?

137
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:33,150
What are you doing here?

138
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,550
I came to help you two.

139
00:15:29,180 --> 00:15:31,310
Where is my brother?

140
00:15:32,630 --> 00:15:35,060
We will look for him.

141
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:39,220
Don't think about anything right now and get some rest.

142
00:15:40,970 --> 00:15:43,430
He must blame me.

143
00:15:43,430 --> 00:15:45,880
I asked him to come with me.

144
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:48,720
It is a disease.

145
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:52,120
We can only stand our ground until there is a treatment.

146
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:56,180
Colonel, the treatment is almost ready, right?

147
00:16:08,530 --> 00:16:12,220
These are sleeping pills. Take one whenever you need one.

148
00:16:20,150 --> 00:16:23,830
Take one now and get some rest.

149
00:16:49,230 --> 00:16:51,730
Let's go outside and talk.

150
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:03,280
Can't you comfort her when she is struggling?

151
00:17:04,320 --> 00:17:05,870
Why did you shoot him?

152
00:17:05,870 --> 00:17:10,560
Kim Seung Beom. He was more than capable of communicating with us.

153
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:12,900
There are tons of people who lost their families on the outside.

154
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:15,460
A mom is biting her child, and a husband is biting his wife.

155
00:17:15,460 --> 00:17:20,090
If you don't want to lose someone close to you, you shouldn't hesitate, either, Yoon Sae Bom.

156
00:17:22,460 --> 00:17:25,110
This isn't healing. Why is that?

157
00:17:25,110 --> 00:17:28,750
I know you looked at me when I was giving her water so tell me the truth.

158
00:17:28,750 --> 00:17:32,730
It means the virus is still present in your body. Sort of like debris.

159
00:17:32,730 --> 00:17:34,330
Could I end up biting people?

160
00:17:34,330 --> 00:17:36,820
That is why I wanted to draw your blood every two weeks.

161
00:17:36,820 --> 00:17:38,660
We have to keep checking.

162
00:17:38,660 --> 00:17:40,560
Is that why you came here?

163
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:42,820
To draw my blood?

164
00:17:47,330 --> 00:17:50,300
- It is because of Seo Yoon's parents. 
 - Is something wrong?

165
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:52,280
Her father has been infected.

166
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:56,690
Her mother is fine, but she desperately misses her daughter.

167
00:17:56,690 --> 00:17:58,690
Then you came to take Seo Yoon with you?

168
00:17:58,690 --> 00:18:02,860
The Madman Rabies situation is worsening not only in our country but globally.

169
00:18:02,860 --> 00:18:05,220
I have some news about the follow-up measures for the apartment, too,

170
00:18:05,220 --> 00:18:08,480
so let's gather the residents after making sure the building is safe.

171
00:18:23,700 --> 00:18:25,310
My Lord...

172
00:18:25,310 --> 00:18:27,230
Is it over?

173
00:18:28,990 --> 00:18:32,100
You said they become normal once they drink blood.

174
00:18:32,100 --> 00:18:35,490
Maybe he bit someone and went home after coming to his senses.

175
00:18:36,550 --> 00:18:39,130
 Is everyone okay in there?

176
00:18:39,130 --> 00:18:41,100
 Open the door!

177
00:18:42,270 --> 00:18:44,170
 Is anyone in there?

178
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:50,430
Hyun, are you okay?

179
00:18:50,430 --> 00:18:53,450
You're not lying after getting bit, are you?

180
00:18:53,450 --> 00:18:56,850
 This isn't the fable "The Wolf And Lamb"!

181
00:18:56,850 --> 00:18:59,620
 Stop rambling nonsense and open the door!

182
00:18:59,620 --> 00:19:02,060
He could be lying. He could!

183
00:19:02,060 --> 00:19:04,860
- Don't you fall for his annoyingly good looks. 
 - My Lord...

184
00:19:04,860 --> 00:19:08,200
 Sir, I can hear everything.

185
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:11,370
 Open the door, Hyung.

186
00:19:12,780 --> 00:19:15,420
What is taking so long to open it?

187
00:19:16,220 --> 00:19:19,680
- Hyung, what is wrong with you? 
 - I almost died!

188
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:21,190
Hey!

189
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:26,400
- Damn it! 
 - This is nuts.

190
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:30,860
Never mind, Hyung. What exactly is going on?

191
00:19:30,860 --> 00:19:34,650
Well, I came to get some cleaners and toothpaste,

192
00:19:34,650 --> 00:19:38,340
but the people with white eyes ran after us from the emergency exit.

193
00:19:38,340 --> 00:19:41,330
- Did anyone get hurt? 
 - No.

194
00:19:41,330 --> 00:19:44,190
Thanks to the pastor...

195
00:19:44,190 --> 00:19:46,720
The pastor has spiritual powers.

196
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:48,460

197
00:20:08,760 --> 00:20:11,520
- What are you talking about now? 
 - It is true!

198
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:12,890
No way...

199
00:20:12,890 --> 00:20:15,590
I didn't have a gun at that point, but...

200
00:20:15,590 --> 00:20:17,730
Oh, right. Hey, where is my gun?

201
00:20:17,730 --> 00:20:21,160
- What? 
 - Gosh, calm down.

202
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:23,350
Who opened the door on the first floor?

203
00:20:23,350 --> 00:20:24,930
Well...

204
00:20:25,660 --> 00:20:30,800
- The jobless guy on the second floor. 
 - He and the supermarket girl left the door open and ran away.

205
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:33,490
Wait, Hyun...

206
00:20:35,310 --> 00:20:37,670
Who shut the door behind me earlier?

207
00:20:48,510 --> 00:20:51,460
Do you think they're okay downstairs?

208
00:20:51,460 --> 00:20:53,300
What if someone got hurt?

209
00:20:53,300 --> 00:20:55,790
All we need to do is make sure our stories match up.

210
00:20:55,790 --> 00:20:58,900
We have to say that we ran away after spotting infected people.

211
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:01,560
No one can hold us responsible then.

212
00:21:07,300 --> 00:21:09,260
Hello.

213
00:21:12,020 --> 00:21:15,470
Miss, you're very pretty.

214
00:21:15,470 --> 00:21:17,470
What is your name?

215
00:21:17,470 --> 00:21:19,760
I'm Lee Bo Ram.

216
00:21:19,760 --> 00:21:22,790
Thank you for the food, Ma'am.

217
00:21:22,790 --> 00:21:24,890
Mom, here.

218
00:21:26,130 --> 00:21:28,760
We are busy. Get out.

219
00:21:28,760 --> 00:21:30,270
All right.

220
00:21:30,270 --> 00:21:34,130
- Let me know if you need anything. 
 - Okay.

221
00:21:34,130 --> 00:21:36,310
Thank you.

222
00:21:46,870 --> 00:21:49,430
Don't the two of them look good together?

223
00:21:50,740 --> 00:21:52,680
Don't get your hopes up.

224
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:56,090
Who would fall for an unemployed guy like that?

225
00:21:56,090 --> 00:21:57,690
Who cares about that?

226
00:21:57,690 --> 00:22:00,260
Look at who I live with.

227
00:22:01,130 --> 00:22:02,690
What?

228
00:22:07,310 --> 00:22:09,000
I think someone is here.

229
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,840
Like I said, just make sure our stories match up.

230
00:22:10,840 --> 00:22:14,300
Don't say anything strange, okay?

231
00:22:14,300 --> 00:22:16,550
We will speak in private. Don't mind us.

232
00:22:16,550 --> 00:22:18,700
No...

233
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:26,090
You two opened the door to the building, right?

234
00:22:26,090 --> 00:22:27,860
What door?

235
00:22:27,860 --> 00:22:30,170
We were here the whole time.

236
00:22:31,330 --> 00:22:34,970
Why? Why, why, why?

237
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:40,270
We went downstairs, and the door was open so we got scared and ran away. Really, really.

238
00:22:40,270 --> 00:22:42,340
Did you get bitten or scratched?

239
00:22:42,340 --> 00:22:45,000
We just got scared and ran away. That is all. Really.

240
00:22:47,860 --> 00:22:51,220
I'm fine, too.

241
00:22:53,880 --> 00:22:56,250
Why did you go down to the first floor?

242
00:23:11,520 --> 00:23:12,770
Did you go out because of this?

243
00:23:12,770 --> 00:23:18,850
Gosh, give it to me. I have to do my show. I put my life on the line for that. Ouch!

244
00:23:24,040 --> 00:23:27,880
Someone is missing because of you.

245
00:23:27,880 --> 00:23:33,320
If you're human, you should have a sense of responsibility, at least.

246
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:38,930
Is everyone okay?

247
00:23:38,930 --> 00:23:40,720
Well, for now.

248
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:45,050
Geez, I barely held myself back from wanting to beat him up.

249
00:23:45,050 --> 00:23:46,840
Where is Han Tae Seok?

250
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:50,530
He went to the rooftop. He is looking for infected people.

251
00:23:53,040 --> 00:23:54,630
Is something wrong?

252
00:23:54,630 --> 00:23:59,310
Seo Yoon's father has been infected.

253
00:23:59,310 --> 00:24:01,870
That is why he came.

254
00:24:07,610 --> 00:24:08,940
I'm here to help

255
00:24:08,940 --> 00:24:10,450
so rest assured.

256
00:24:10,450 --> 00:24:12,960
Yes, it looks that way.

257
00:24:13,660 --> 00:24:15,390
Did any infected come up here?

258
00:24:15,390 --> 00:24:19,640
Two of them came up, and I told them to go down that way.

259
00:24:28,620 --> 00:24:31,250
Oh, I broke that.

260
00:24:48,300 --> 00:24:51,770
When you told them to go down, did they just go?

261
00:25:05,350 --> 00:25:07,700
There aren't any infected people inside the apartment.

262
00:25:07,700 --> 00:25:12,310
It looks like Na Soo Min went outside after being infected.

263
